# FlashOS FAT32 permission overlay (PERMS.TAB)
#
# Format: NAME MODE UID GID
#   NAME — 8.3 basename in the FAT32 root (matched case-insensitively)
#   MODE — octal permission word (low 9 bits)
#   UID / GID — decimal owner ids
#
# Parsed once at mount time by the kernel (crates/kernel/src/overlay.rs
# wired through crates/kernel/src/fat32_backend.rs). Unannotated files keep
# the 0666 root:root default; the shadow file floors at 0600 even without
# this overlay. This file protects itself through its own entry.
#
# Seeded onto the QEMU SD image by scripts/make_test_disk.sh and onto a
# real card by `flash build -d`.
PERMS.TAB 0600 0 0
SHADOW 0600 0 0
ROUNDTR.DAT 0666 0 0
ROUNDTR.MAG 0666 0 0
